1. Virtualization (Old Way)

In VM:

Hardware
 └── Hypervisor
      ├── Guest OS (Ubuntu)
      │     └── App
      ├── Guest OS (CentOS)
      │     └── App


❌ Problems:

Each VM needs full OS (1–2 GB)

Slow boot (minutes)

High RAM/CPU usage

Heavy maintenance



2. Containerization (Docker Way)
Hardware
 └── Host OS
      └── Docker Engine
           ├── Container 1 → App
           ├── Container 2 → App


✅ Benefits:

Share host kernel

Size MBs not GBs

Start in seconds

Portable

Same on dev → prod
